Installation react:

1. NodeJS from Official site or Sparsh Downloads
2. C:\Users\userName>npm install babel -g
3. C:\Users\userName>npm install webpack -g
4. C:\Users\userName>npm install webpack-dev-server -g

create a folder on desktop named reactdemos.
5. C:\Users\userName>Desktop\reactdemos>npm init
 
 npm init command will create the package.json file 
 Just replace for 'scripts'  for package.json as below:
"scripts": { 
"start": "webpack-dev-server --hot"
}


6. C:\Users\userName>Desktop\reactdemos>npm install webpack
7. C:\Users\userName>Desktop\reactdemos>npm install webpack-dev-server

8. C:\Users\userName>Desktop\reactdemos>npm install react --save
9. C:\Users\userName>Desktop\reactdemos>npm install react-dom --save
10. C:\Users\userName>Desktop\reactdemos>npm install babel-core
11. C:\Users\userName>Desktop\reactdemos>npm install babel-loader
12. C:\Users\userName>Desktop\reactdemos>npm install babel-preset-react
13. C:\Users\userName>Desktop\reactdemos>npm install babel-preset-es2015


Execution:
1.Copy  the shared demo folder (Eg. folder named '1') to reactdemos folder.
2.Replace the package.json inside this with  the package.json you have created inside reactdemos folder

To run the demo,  from node command prompt:
1.cd <path of reactdemos folder>
2.Type D: and press enter
3.Type 'npm start' and enter
4.To check Output from  browser, type localhost:7777 and hit enter.

